        { lines: ["{{receiverName}}, I see you in your struggle, and I want you to know: you are going to be okay.", "Not because the struggle isn't real, but because you have what it takes to move through it.", "I've watched you face difficult things before, and you've always found your way.", "This time won't be different in that regard—you will find your way again.", "But while you're in it, I want to be a voice reminding you of your own strength.", "Please hold onto my belief in you."] },
        { lines: ["The fact that you're struggling means you're trying, you're caring, you're engaged with something that matters.", "People who struggle are people who have raised their standards, who are pushing for something more.", "That struggle is evidence of your commitment and your character.", "Don't let difficulty convince you that you're doing something wrong—you're doing something brave.", "I see the effort you're making even when nobody else is watching.", "Keep going, {{receiverName}}."] },
        { lines: ["I remember {{specialMemory}}, and I remember how you handled it with such grace.", "You're someone who can face hard things. You're someone who has already proven resilience.", "That same person who got through that moment is still inside you, still capable, still strong.", "You haven't lost that strength—you're just tired right now and that's okay.", "Tiredness isn't defeat. It's just the natural response to carrying something heavy.", "Rest when you need to, and know that your strength will return."] },
        { lines: ["You don't have to have all the answers right now, {{receiverName}}.", "You don't have to see the whole path forward or know exactly how this ends.", "What you have to do is take the next right step, make the next good choice, do the next true thing.", "That's all anyone can do when they're in the thick of it.", "Focus on today, on this moment, on what's in front of you.", "Tomorrow will take care of itself if you faithfully handle today."] },
        { lines: ["I need you to know that your struggle doesn't make you less-than, {{receiverName}}.", "It makes you human and alive and engaged with something that matters.", "The people who never struggle are people who aren't trying, who aren't growing, who aren't reaching.", "You're reaching, and that's beautiful even though it's exhausting.", "Keep reaching, even with tired arms and a doubtful heart.", "I believe in you completely."] },
        { lines: ["Let yourself ask for help, {{receiverName}}.", "You don't have to carry everything alone—that's not how humans are designed.", "The people who love you want to help. Please let them.", "Asking for help isn't weakness—it's wisdom and it's courage.", "You've helped others when they struggled—receive that gift when others offer it to you.", "I'm here, and I'm not the only one."] },
        { lines: ["Your fear is real and valid, {{receiverName}}, and you can move forward anyway.", "Courage isn't the absence of fear—it's moving ahead despite being afraid.", "You can feel terrified and still take the next step.", "You can doubt and still move forward.", "Fear is just information—it's not a verdict on your capability.", "Don't let fear write your story. You get to write it."] },
        { lines: ["This season will not last forever, {{receiverName}}, even though it feels eternal right now.", "Everything changes. Everything moves. Nothing stays hard forever.", "This difficult chapter will give way to a different chapter.", "You will feel different, see differently, be different than you are right now.", "There is light ahead that you cannot yet see from where you stand.", "Hold on. This is not the end—it's just a difficult part of the journey."] },
        { lines: ["You're stronger than you're giving yourself credit for, {{receiverName}}.", "You've survived 100% of your worst days so far.", "Every day you thought you couldn't make it through, you made it through.", "That track record of survival is powerful evidence that you have what you need.", "You have already proven that you're capable of getting through hard things.", "Trust your own resilience."] },
        { lines: ["The world might measure success by certain outcomes, {{receiverName}}, but I measure it differently.", "I measure it by the effort you're making, by your faithfulness, by your refusal to give up.", "I measure it by the way you're still trying, still showing up, still hoping.", "That's the kind of success that actually matters.", "That's the kind of success that builds character and shapes a life well-lived.", "You're successful, {{receiverName}}, because you keep trying."] },
        { lines: ["Your struggle is not a sign of failure, {{receiverName}}", "It's a sign that you're human and engaged and growing.", "It's evidence that you're committed to something that matters.", "Yes, it's hard. Yes, it's exhausting. But you're doing it anyway.", "That's not weakness—that's the truest form of strength.", "I see you, and I'm proud of you."] },
        { lines: ["Please be kind to yourself, {{receiverName}}, especially during this difficult time.", "Stop beating yourself up about what you're not doing perfectly.", "Show yourself the same compassion you show to people you love when they're struggling.", "You're doing the best you can with what you have right now, and that's enough.", "Perfectionism is not your friend right now—self-compassion is.", "Treat yourself with the gentleness you deserve."] },
        { lines: ["This difficulty is teaching you things you need to know, {{receiverName}}.", "It's revealing your strength, your capacity to love, your resilience.", "You're becoming more compassionate, more humble, more real through this struggle.", "Years from now you'll see how this hard time shaped you into something beautiful.", "The lessons you're learning now will serve you well later.", "Trust the process, even when you don't understand it."] },
        { lines: ["You are worthy of love and support and good things, {{receiverName}}, not because of what you do but because of who you are.", "You deserve kindness from others and especially from yourself.", "You don't have to earn love by perfect performance or endless productivity.", "You're worthy simply because you exist.", "Let people show you kindness without feeling you have to repay it somehow.", "You deserve the goodness you're extending to others."] },
        { lines: ["The people who love you are watching your struggle with admiration, {{receiverName}}.", "We see your effort. We see your courage. We see your faithfulness.", "We're not disappointed in you—we're proud of you.", "Your struggle doesn't diminish you in our eyes—it shows us your character.", "You're beautiful in your struggle, {{receiverName}}", "Keep going."] },
        { lines: ["Look for small joys even in this difficult season, {{receiverName}}.", "A good meal, a moment of laughter, the sun on your face, a hug from someone you love.", "These small things are gifts. They're proof that beauty still exists alongside struggle.", "Taking care of yourself spiritually and emotionally and physically matters.", "These small moments of beauty and goodness are part of how you survive hard times.", "Notice them. Savor them. Let them sustain you."] },
        { lines: ["You are not your circumstances, {{receiverName}}", "You're not defined by this difficult time you're going through.", "This is something happening to you, not the totality of who you are.", "You contain strength and weakness, wisdom and foolishness, hope and fear.", "The circumstances don't get to tell the whole story about who you are.", "Beyond this difficulty, you're still whole, you're still valuable, you're still you."] },
        { lines: ["Tomorrow is a new day, {{receiverName}}, with new possibilities and new mercies.", "Whatever happened today, whatever went wrong, tomorrow is a fresh start.", "You don't have to get it all right today—you just have to get through today.", "Then tomorrow you get another chance, another day, another opportunity.", "That's the gift of each new day—the chance to begin again.", "I believe that better days are ahead for you."] },
        { lines: ["I want you to know that I'm proud of you, {{receiverName}}, truly proud.", "Proud of the way you're facing this, of your effort, of your courage.", "Proud of you even on days when you don't feel proud of yourself.", "Proud of the person you're becoming through all of this.", "Your struggle doesn't diminish your worth—it displays your character.", "Keep going. You're doing better than you think."] },
        { lines: ["I'm holding hope for you when you can't hold it for yourself, {{receiverName}}.", "I believe in your ability to move through this and into something better.", "I see your strength even on the days when you feel weak.", "I see your courage even on the days when you feel afraid.", "Lean on my belief in you until you can find your own belief again.", "You will get through this. I believe that with all my heart."] }
